{
  "text": "Assume a UCA with P array elements arranged uniformly around its perimeter of radius r, each with angle \u03b8 i = 2\u03c0 \u00b7 i/P with i \u2208 [0, P \u2212 1] as illustrated in Figure 1 . Note that the distance between two consecutive array elements should not be larger than \u03bb/2 to avoid spatial aliasing effects [CITATION_1] . Assume that the CIR between the Tx and the center of the UCA is composed by K multipath plane waves. The channel frequency response is:",
